8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1096, L.D. 1655, “An Act to Allow the
10 Keeping of Chickens on Private Residential Property”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 7 MRSA §219-D is enacted to read:
14 §219-D. Keeping chickens on residential property
15 A county or municipality may not adopt a regulation or ordinance that prohibits a
16 person from keeping chickens on that person's residential property. For purposes of this
17 section, "chicken" means a female domesticated bird that is raised for meat or eggs and
18 does not include a fully mature domesticated male chicken. This section may not be
19 construed to limit the home rule authority of a municipality.'
20 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
21 number to read consecutively.
22 SUMMARY
2233 This amendment replaces the bill. The amendment clarifies that a county or
2244 municipality may not adopt a regulation or ordinance that prohibits a person from keeping
2255 chickens on that person's residential property.
26 The amendment also removes from the bill requirements relating to the number of
27 chickens on a person's property, coop specifications, square footage of secure outdoor
28 space per chicken and security. The amendment defines "chicken" as a domesticated bird
29 that is raised for meat or eggs and does not include a fully mature domesticated male
30 chicken.
